cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and understanding of pragmatic inferences. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques (LSTM-based sentence encoder) to predict human inference strength ratings. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves training a model to learn associations between linguistic cues and inference strength ratings. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve discussions on the computational complexity of the model used. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is the least likely category as the paper does not seem to involve any discussions on sound or audio processing.
